To convert the GLSL specular highlight to a Gaussian specular, you can modify the formula as follows:

1. Define the Gaussian function:
   ```
   float gaussian(float x, float sigma)
   {
       return exp(-(x * x) / (2.0 * sigma * sigma));
   }
   ```

2. Replace the `specularIntensity` calculation with the Gaussian function:
   ```
   float specularIntensity = gaussian(max(dot(in_fNormal, normalize(lightDirection + viewDirection)), 0.0f), uMaterial.shininess);
   ```

This modification will calculate the specular intensity using a Gaussian distribution instead of the simple power function. The `uMaterial.shininess` parameter can control the spread of the Gaussian curve, with higher values creating a tighter, more concentrated specular highlight.

