vec3 halfVector = normalize(lightDirection + viewDirection);
float NdotH = max(dot(in_fNormal, halfVector), 0.0);

// Calculate Gaussian specular intensity
float sigma = sqrt(uMaterial.shininess);
float exponent = -(NdotH * NdotH) / (2.0 * sigma * sigma);
float specularIntensity = exp(exponent);

```

In this code, we calculate the half vector (vector between the light direction and view direction). Then, we calculate the dot product between the surface normal (in_fNormal) and the half vector (NdotH). Finally, we use the dot product angle and material shininess value (which serves as the standard deviation) to calculate the Gaussian specular intensity.

Make sure to use this modified code and pass appropriate values for uViewPosition, in_fPositionWorld, lightDirection, and uMaterial.shininess for accurate results.

